cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.EC, cs.DS, cs.CE 

This paper deals with the problem of pricing products in an online marketplace, specifically Airbnb Experiences. It involves learning distributions of values of items and using them to price the items in a search event. This problem falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves retrieving and ranking items based on query relevance models. It also involves machine learning techniques for learning value distributions, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The problem of pricing items in a competitive marketplace can also be seen as an application of Game Theory (cs.GT) and Economics (cs.EC). The paper also mentions aggregation of results over searches, which involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and optimization techniques (cs.CE).
